.TH "slim_get_device" 9 "slim_get_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
slim_get_device \- get handle to a device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct slim_device *" slim_get_device
.BI "(struct slim_controller *ctrl "  ","
.BI "struct slim_eaddr *e_addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
Controller on which this device will be added/queried
.IP "e_addr" 12
Enumeration address of the device to be queried
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to a device if it has already reported. Creates a new
device and returns pointer to it if the device has not yet enumerated.
